1 2. The study must invite participation from an institution of higher education for
2 assistance in evaluating social interests and community acceptance of potential siting
3 locations.
4 3. The committee must consist of:
5 a. Two members representing the energy industry, appointed by the legislative
6 management;
7 b. One member appointed by the public service commission;
8 c. One member appointed by the industrial commission;
9 d. Three members of the house of representatives selected by the majority leader of
10 the house of representatives, two of whom must represent the majority faction of
11 the house of representatives and one of whom must represent the minority
12 faction of the house of representatives; and
13 e. Three members of the senate selected by the majority leader of the senate, two
14 of whom must represent the majority faction of the senate and one of whom must
15 represent the minority faction of the senate.
16 4. The legislative management shall report its findings and recommendations, together
17 with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to the seventieth
18 legislative assembly.
19 5. a. A member of the committee who is not a state employee is entitled to
20 reimbursement for mileage and expenses as provided by law for state officers
21 and employees, to be paid by the legislative council.
22 b. A state employee who is a member of the committee is entitled to receive that
23 employee's regular salary and is entitled to reimbursement for mileage and
24 expenses to be paid by the employing agency.
25 c. A member of the committee who is a member of the legislative assembly is
26 entitled to receive per diem compensation at the rate provided under section
27 54-35-10 for each day performing official duties of the committee. The legislative
28 council shall pay the per diem compensation and reimbursement for travel and
29 expenses as provided by law for any member of the committee who is a member
30 of the legislative assembly.
