1 SECTION 2. APPROPRIATION - LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL - ADVANCED NUCLEAR
2 ENERGY STUDY - MATCHING FUNDS - ONE-TIME FUNDING. There is appropriated out of
3 any moneys in the general fund in the state treasury, not otherwise appropriated, the sum of
4 $500,000, or so much of the sum as may be necessary, and from special funds derived from
5 grants or donations from nonstate sources, the sum of $500,000, or so much of the sum as may
6 be necessary, to the legislative council for the purpose of contracting for consulting services for
7 the study provided for in section 1 of this Act, for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and
8 ending June 30, 2027. The legislative council shall seek matching funds from the private sector
9 to the extent available to assist with the cost of the project. The funding provided in this section
10 is considered a one-time funding item.
